# 2048 — product context

## Default experience (non-negotiable)

- The app must **always** ship with a **plain, original classic 2048**: **4×4 grid**, standard merge rules, no alternate topology as the default.
- **First load**, **New Game**, and any **reset to defaults** must use this classic board unless the player has explicitly chosen another layout in-session or via a saved preference.
- **Board size** is a custom pill dropdown in the header next to **New Game** (4×4–8×8). **4×4 remains the classic default** for new visitors; preference in `localStorage` (`preferredBoardSize`). Hex or other topologies stay separate.

## Stack and layout

- **Vanilla** HTML (`index.html`), CSS (`style.css`), ES modules-free JS (`game.js` and siblings). No build step.
- Core game: `game.js` (`SIZE = 4`), grid in `#board-cells` / `#tiles-container`, events `game:new`, `game:move`, `game:end`, `game:merge2048`.
- Backend: Supabase (auth, games, achievements, leaderboard). PWA: `manifest.json`, `sw.js`.

## Brand and UI

- **Accent / brand orange**: `#FF6B2B` (`--orange`), hot `#ff3d00` (`--orange-hot`). Used for logo glow, primary CTAs, active states, 2048 tile, focus rings.
- **Surfaces**: page `#0f0f0f`, board `#1a1a1a`, cells `#242424`, muted text via `--text-muted` / `--text-dim`.
- **Typography**: **Bricolage Grotesque** (logo, scores, tiles) · **Geist** (UI copy, modals).
- **Tile ramp**: warm beiges → oranges → golds → purple (1024) → brand orange shimmer (2048) → conic “galaxy” (4096+). Match existing `style.css` selectors when extending values.
- **Tone**: polished dark UI, pill buttons, rounded board/tiles (`--radius-board`, `--radius-tile`), subtle orange board glow.

When adding features (e.g. board size picker), preserve this visual system and keep the classic 4×4 path the simplest, most prominent default.
